<subSubSection id="79DA65243624FC06C482D827FF7DB40E" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="317F36AF3624FC06C482D827FC24B7A9" blockId="29.[178,1086,1247,1539]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">
Comment: The original description of this species is based on 
<specimenCount id="27C6FD263624FC06C74BD827FBACB723" box="[891,1027,1304,1326]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" type="female">three females</specimenCount>
from Cádiz province (
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E3624FC06C552D809FE53B741" author="ASSING V" box="[354,508,1334,1356]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" pagination="1105 - 1124" refId="ref20068" refString="ASSING V. (2010 a): Four new species and additional records of Staphylinidae from Spain, primarily from the south (Insecta: Coleoptera). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 42 (2): 1105 - 1124." type="journal article" year="2010">ASSING 2010a</bibRefCitation>
). In the meantime, the above specimens have become available, among them a male. So far, all the specimens have been collected in December and January. It seems likely that, like the 
<typeStatus id="EE7B880D3624FC06C66DD84EFD26B78B" box="[605,649,1393,1414]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">type</typeStatus>
material, the above material was collected during periods of heavy rain. The male sexual characters are as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="317F36AF3624FC06C4F7D88BFF7DB40E" blockId="29.[178,1086,1247,1539]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">
: sternite VIII much longer than broad, posterior margin obtusely angled in the middle (
<figureCitation id="A9FB2A2A3624FC06C48AD8EFFEA8B7EB" box="[186,263,1488,1510]" captionStart="Figs 51-57" captionStartId="30.[178,218,1011,1031]" captionTargetBox="[188,1081,218,974]" captionTargetId="figure-266@30.[178,1085,212,984]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="Figs 51-57: Oxypoda defossa ASSING (51-53) and &quot;O.&quot; weiratheri BERNHAUER (54-57; 55-56: lectotype): (51) male sternite VIII; (52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (53, 56) paramere; (54) habitus; (55) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (57) spermatheca. Scale bars: 54: 0.5 mm; 51: 0.2 mm; 52-53, 55-57: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6483843" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6483843/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
); median lobe of aedeagus conspicuously slender (
<figureCitation id="A9FB2A2A3624FC06C724D8EFFCCDB7EB" box="[788,866,1488,1510]" captionStart="Figs 51-57" captionStartId="30.[178,218,1011,1031]" captionTargetBox="[188,1081,218,974]" captionTargetId="figure-266@30.[178,1085,212,984]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="Figs 51-57: Oxypoda defossa ASSING (51-53) and &quot;O.&quot; weiratheri BERNHAUER (54-57; 55-56: lectotype): (51) male sternite VIII; (52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (53, 56) paramere; (54) habitus; (55) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (57) spermatheca. Scale bars: 54: 0.5 mm; 51: 0.2 mm; 52-53, 55-57: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6483843" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6483843/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
); paramere as in 
<figureCitation id="A9FB2A2A3624FC06C025D8EFFF61B40E" captionStart="Figs 51-57" captionStartId="30.[178,218,1011,1031]" captionTargetBox="[188,1081,218,974]" captionTargetId="figure-266@30.[178,1085,212,984]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="Figs 51-57: Oxypoda defossa ASSING (51-53) and &quot;O.&quot; weiratheri BERNHAUER (54-57; 55-56: lectotype): (51) male sternite VIII; (52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (53, 56) paramere; (54) habitus; (55) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (57) spermatheca. Scale bars: 54: 0.5 mm; 51: 0.2 mm; 52-53, 55-57: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6483843" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6483843/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
